Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '163'. Name Klenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0164.34.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (116)
